--- a/system/sepolicy/private/mac_permissions.xml
+++ b/system/sepolicy/private/mac_permissions.xml
@@ -47,6 +47,13 @@
 -->

+    <!-- Platform key with package-specific seinfo overrides -->
+    <signer signature="@PLATFORM" >
+      <package name="com.android.providers.media.module">
+        <seinfo value="media" />
+      </package>
+    </signer>
+
     <!-- Platform dev key in AOSP -->
     <signer signature="@PLATFORM" >
       <seinfo value="platform" />

Description: Fix SD card mount by giving MediaProvider the correct SELinux domain.
MediaProvider (inside com.android.mediaprovider APEX) is signed with the platform key
but needs seinfo=media to get the mediaprovider_app SELinux domain for FUSE access.
Without this, MediaProvider runs as platform_app which lacks /dev/fuse access,
causing vold public volume mount to fail.

Must be placed BEFORE the global platform seinfo entry.

File: system/sepolicy/private/mac_permissions.xml
